1 B. A waiver to the provisions of subsection A of this section
2 shall be granted if the parent or legal guardian of a student
3 provides written consent.
4 C. As used in this section, “corporal punishment” means the
5 deliberate infliction of physical pain by hitting, paddling,
6 spanking, slapping, or any other physical force used as a means of
7 discipline.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
9 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
